---
# Symphony-TS workflow contract. Copy to WORKFLOW.md and customize.
tracker:
  kind: plane
  # Local self-hosted Plane instance — start it with `pnpm plane:up` (see infra/plane/README.md).
  endpoint: http://localhost
  # Reads PLANE_API_KEY from the environment when api_key is unset or "$PLANE_API_KEY".
  api_key: $PLANE_API_KEY
  # workspace_slug: from the workspace URL `/<workspace-slug>/`. project_id: the project UUID.
  workspace_slug: "your-workspace-slug"
  project_id: "your-project-uuid"
  # Symphony custom flow — configure these state names in the Plane project's workflow.
  active_states: [Todo, In Progress, Rework, Merging]
  terminal_states: [Done, Cancelled]
  # Note: "Human Review" is intentionally NOT active — it parks work for a human.

# Switchable projects for the dashboard's project switcher. The ACTIVE project is whichever
# project_id/repo sit in `tracker`/`workspace` above; this registry is the set you can switch to
# (and what "+ New project" appends to). Each entry = a Plane project_id + its own repo folder.
# Switching live re-points the orchestrator (no restart). Managed from the dashboard — listed here
# so it survives restarts.
projects:
  # - name: Backend
  #   project_id: "another-project-uuid"
  #   repo: ~/code/backend
  #   identifier: BE          # optional, informational

polling:
  interval_ms: 5000

workspace:
  # Single shared repo (local path or git URL); every ticket gets a worktree off it.
  repo: git@github.com:your-org/your-repo.git
  root: ~/code/symphony-workspaces
  branch_prefix: "symphony/"

hooks:
  # Runs once per new worktree. Install deps here.
  after_create: |
    if [ -f package.json ]; then npm ci || npm install; fi
  timeout_ms: 120000

agent:
  backend: claude-sdk        # claude-sdk | claude-cli | codex-cli | opencode-cli
  permission_mode: bypassPermissions   # full autonomy (high-trust)
  max_concurrent_agents: 5
  max_turns: 20
  max_continuations: 50       # cap consecutive continuations before blocking the issue (0 = unlimited)
  # model: claude-opus-4-8   # optional override
  # max_budget_usd: 5        # optional per-turn budget cap (claude-sdk)
  # tmux: true               # CLI backends only: run each turn in a tmux session you can
                             # `tmux attach -t symphony-<id>`; raw stdout is logged to logs_root.
                             # No effect on the in-process claude-sdk backend.

# Root for raw tmux session logs (run.jsonl/err.log per turn). Default: <tmpdir>/symphony_logs.
# Override at launch with `--logs-root <dir>`.
# logs_root: ~/code/symphony-logs

server:
  port: 4500                 # enables the dashboard at http://127.0.0.1:4500/
---

You are an autonomous engineer working on Plane issue {{ issue.identifier }} in an isolated git
worktree on branch `symphony/{{ issue.identifier }}`.

Title: {{ issue.title }}
{% if issue.description %}
{{ issue.description }}
{% else %}
(No description provided.)
{% endif %}

Your job:
1. Implement the change end-to-end. Keep edits scoped to this issue.
2. Run the project's build/tests/lints and make them pass before finishing.
3. Commit your work to the current `symphony/{{ issue.identifier }}` branch with a concise message.
   Do NOT push or open a pull request — commits stay local for now.
4. Move the Plane issue to "Human Review" so a human can take it from here, and post a short
   comment summarizing what you changed. Use the `mcp__symphony__tracker_api` tool (see below).
5. If you are blocked and genuinely need a human decision, say so explicitly and stop — do not guess.

You have a `mcp__symphony__tracker_api` tool that runs ONE REST call against this Plane project with
Symphony's configured auth. Paths are relative to this project and you cannot leave it. Plane moves
an issue by setting its **state UUID**, so resolve the id first. Call the tool once per operation:

a. List this project's workflow states and find the one named "Human Review":
   `{ "method": "GET", "path": "/states/" }`
   → in the response, find the entry whose `name` == "Human Review" and take its `id`.
b. Move this issue to that state (note the trailing slash):
   `{ "method": "PATCH", "path": "/work-items/{{ issue.id }}/", "body": { "state": "<STATE_UUID>" } }`
c. Post your summary as an HTML comment:
   `{ "method": "POST", "path": "/work-items/{{ issue.id }}/comments/", "body": { "comment_html": "<p>…</p>" } }`
